<div id="content">
	<h1>For Non-Scientists<br /></h1>
<p>&nbsp;Diseases such as heart attack can occasionally run in families and doctors think that this may be due to the inheritance of some genes.</p>
<p>We are trying to identify some of these genes in order to:</p>
<p>1) understand the causes of heart disease so new preventative measures and treatments can be developed, and</p>
<p>2) estimate risk based on genetic profiles. To carry out this research, we need to collect DNA samples from thousands of patients and compare them with healthy volunteers.</p>
<p>Several genes, that each make a tiny change to the overall risk of suffering a heart attack have been identified and we are following this research up to see if new treatments might be possible in the future.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p></div>
